    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="390"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d390">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.796/897</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Australian Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="25" xml:id="d390fn25">Written at the Australian Legation.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-05">5 June,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Cordell Hull</hi>: I refer to Mr. Winant’s letter
                    to me of 4th May,<note n="26" xml:id="d390fn26">See telegram 3548, May 3, 11
                        p.m., to London, <ref target="#pg_464">p. 464</ref>.</note> in which he
                    enquired whether I would be disposed to hold exploratory talks on postwar
                    international aviation in Washington on my return from London.</p>
                <p>Under date 13th May I sent an interim reply.<note n="27" xml:id="d390fn27">See
                        telegram 3934. May 15, from London, <ref target="#pg_476">p.
                        476</ref>.</note> I now desire to confirm that it would not be practicable
                    for me to arrange for Australia to be represented at the suggested talks at the
                    present time. <pb facs="0497" n="487" xml:id="pg_487"/> I shall however examine
                    the matter immediately on my arrival in Australia and will advise you further as
                    soon as I am able.</p>
                <p>Yours faithfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Curtin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
